Absolutely loved this place. Very friendly and peaceful environment.  I had never had a server so polite and professional. We had a complete 5 course meal and he did not rush us which ultimately lets you enjoy the wonderful food and view even more! The view was also amazing over looking the water and college. The main part of this review. The food- We started with a tenderloin carppacio. Spot on and a must try appetizer. My wife is not a fan of raw beef until this, Malio's won her palate over. Then we got the must try watermelon salad, Again amazing! The watermelon matches very well with the goat cheese. Followed by the french onion soup which was also very tasty and the bread from earlier was great being dipped in it. The main course- 10oz prime filet cooked medium rare was hands down the best steak i have ever had! This steak melted in my mouth and was cooked to perfection! My overall experience at Malio's Couldn't have been any better and I highly recommend this place and will definitely be coming back!

I don't understand why people go to Burns when Malios exists in Tampa.  The food is better. The views are better. The atmosphere isn't an outdated good ol boys club.  All that to say, I think Malios is one of, if not the best, place to order a steak in Tampa. The comparison to Burns is only because that's generally the biggest competition.  You'll spend some money, but it's worth it. Make it an anniversary dinner or birthday celebration. Or hey, if you have the flex, make it a Tuesday dinner. It's worth it.

It took 15 minutes to get my new filet and it came back black and blue. Manager proceeded to argue with me and told me my original filet was medium rare. We are from Dallas Texas. We eat steak 3-4x a week. So it is insulting, ridiculous in fact, to ague about how to cook steak - of any cut - to a desired preference. They did comp my filet and the bottle of wine, but what I wanted was a nice steak dinner with my daughter. Going back to Texas really disappointed.

The food was elegant, delicious and perfectly prepared with beautiful presentation. We loved the a la carte shareable side dishes to go along with our entrees. It added great variety to the meal.  Malio's is an amazing dining experience.  The only drawback is downtown parking. The valet lot is small and fills quickly. It's easier to just go to the parking garage under the Sykes building, but it's not well signed for the restaurant for first time visitors. Malio's parking is near the back of the garage and the restaurant validates your parking.

Looking for a mediocre experience while paying for more? It's not that anything in particular went horribly wrong but, Malio's was held to higher standards due to their location, atmosphere and price point. Just disappointed with overall execution. Kitchen was okay but seems to be getting by with the bare minimum. The picture of my filet speaks for itself. In all fairness the seasoning and temperature was on point, but this is something I can expect from a local roadhouse without the inflated price. Waitstaff and overall front of house interaction is really to blame here. Any business can have an "off" day but the complete disregard for basic service is a reflection of management. This is the first time I've ever given less than 3 stars. As a local resident I hope this review inspires Malio's to step up their game. If not, I welcome the next chef and restaurant manager to take over and allow this location to showcase it's true potential. A chain is only as strong as it's weakest link.
